The paper deals with the classification and verification of handwritten signatures, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach uses information theory quantifiers, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of One-Class Support Vector Machines, which is a technique commonly used in anomaly detection (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in biometrics and forensic science, which are areas of research in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
